"First cases of Omicron variant found in countries including Mauritius - Xinhua News Agency."
"Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 12 - According to reports from Xinhua News Agency's foreign correspondents: Mauritius, Cyprus, and Malawi have recently reported the first cases of infections with the new coronavirus Omicron variant."
"Mauritius reported its first two cases of Omicron variant infections on the 10th."
"According to the Minister of Health Kailash Jugutpal, one of the infected individuals is a tourist who arrived in Mauritius from South Africa on November 27th; the other infected individual is a local resident of Mauritius who tested positive for the virus after coming into contact with someone who recently returned from South Africa and was tested positive on November 30th."
"After being treated in isolation at the hospital, the results of the nucleic acid tests for both infected individuals turned negative and they have now returned to their respective residences."
"The Ministry of Health in Cyprus announced on the 10th the country's first three confirmed cases of Omicron variant infections."
"These three individuals are all students who returned from overseas travel earlier this month. Since they all have mild symptoms, they were not hospitalized for treatment."
"In order to prevent the spread of the Omicron variant, the government of Cyprus is continuously increasing its preventive measures."
"From December 6th to January 10th, all travelers over the age of 12 who enter Cyprus by plane will be required to undergo a nucleic acid test at the airport at their own expense."
"The Ministry of Health in Cyprus also announced on the 10th that it will start vaccinating children between the ages of 5 and 11 with the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine."
The Health Minister of Malawi, Kuni Zempaka, announced on the 9th that the country had reported its first three cases of infection with the Omicron variant of the COVID-19 virus.
The Ministry of Health in Malawi announced that three cases of the new variant of the coronavirus (Omnicoke variant) have been found after conducting genomic sequencing on twelve positive samples collected from November 9th to December 2nd.